 Days Shall You Labor: Jewish Perspectives on Finding Meaning in Work -- tIndex0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aThis book presents a group of distinguished scholars who examine key themes in Jewish religious life. Their essays revolve around the dimensions of rabbinic, intellectual, cultural, communal, educational, political, and social leadership, as well as a reflective look at one of the most tragic events in Jewish experience, towards the hope of repairing the world and not repeating such evil. The scholarship reproduced in this volume captures the essence of Touro University: remembering the past, perpetuating the rich historic Jewish tradition of tolerance and dignity, and managing the delicate ballet of serving humanity and the Jewish community at the same time. These papers are expressive of the Jewish commitment to intellectual inquiry, the transmission of knowledge, and the pursuit of social justice.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aHolocaust, Jewish (1939-1945)zPolandvCongresses. 0aJewish leadershipvCongresses. 0aJewish learning and scholarshipvCongresses. 0aJewsxPersecutionszPolandvCongresses. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Jewish Studies.2bisacsh  aHolocaust.  aJewish community.  aJewish education.  aJewish institutions.  aJewish law.  aJewish leadership.  aJewish religion.  aJewish religious continuity and change.  aJewish studies.  aJewish tradition.  aTouro University.1 aBleich, Judith, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBoylan, Stanley L., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrewing, Daniel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEngelberg, Sydney, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/c